03/10/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Major General Virgil Packett officially took over the command of SFOR on Thursday (2 October), vowing that troops would continue their search for war crimes suspects. His mandate will last one year. Packett replaces Lieutenant General William Ward, who has been appointed deputy commander of the US Army in Europe.
In other news, the president of the European Parliament, Pat Cox, addressed the BiH Parliament in Sarajevo on Thursday, encouraging local authorities to continue political and economic reforms to bridge the gap with the EU. Cox said the main criteria for starting accession negotiations with the EU is arresting major war crimes suspects, especially former Bosnian Serb leaders Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic. (Dnevni Avaz, Vecernji List, Oslobodjenje, Dnevni List, Nezavisne Novine - 03/10/03; HINA, SRNA, AFP, FTV, RTRS - 02/10/03)
